LAN 1 also connects directly to Internet. This means that Link to VPN server is only used to link LAN 2.

LAN 2 also connects directly to Internet. This means that Link to VPN server is only used to link LAN 1.

div.div: It is important to know that:

1. If in your LAN 1 You have connected to VPN Server through your router, probably you won't need to configure any route but if you have used any other device to route traffic to VPN probably you should do some routing in your router.
2. If you apply any firewall rules you must know that clients in any remote will be shown as the IP of the Wireguard Peer.
